CHINA-FOCUSED phosphate miner AsiaPhos Limited on Friday said it is looking to acquire the entire stake in gold and copper miner MMJV  in a deal that will constitute a reverse takeover of the former.AsiaPhos plans to issue and allot to the seller its ordinary shares at 0.5 Singapore cent each  totalling either S$72 million or half of the agreed valuation of the target group  whichever is lower.The agreed issue price is at a 75 per cent discount to the weighted average trading price of AsiaPhos shares of 2.17 cents on the market day before AsiaPhos signed the term sheet on Tuesday with Mining and Minerals Industries Holding (MMIH) for the proposed acquisition.The shares where got 0.5 worth man
